<Layout title="Sponsors & Maritime Partners" description="MMBA Regatta sponsors and maritime partners — marinas, yacht clubs, marine businesses, and organizations supporting San Francisco Bay's classic sailing tradition.">

  <div class="hero-band">
    <h1>Sponsors &amp; Maritime Partners</h1>
    <p>The maritime businesses and organizations that make the regatta possible</p>
  </div>

  <main>
    <h1>Regatta Sponsors</h1>

    <p>
      The Master Mariners Regatta has always depended on the generous support of Bay Area maritime businesses, yacht clubs, and organizations. Sponsors receive a custom house flag flown from their sponsored yacht throughout the regatta weekend — a colorful and highly visible tradition on the Bay.
    </p>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Sponsor Flags</h3>
      <p>
        Sponsor flags are a key part of the regatta's maritime tradition. Each sponsor is guided to create a custom house flag in their colors and design, which flies from their sponsored vessel throughout the weekend. Flags are typically 36"×60" nylon, custom-made. Setup cost runs approximately $50 per design; a 36"×60" flag approximately $80–85 plus setup.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Historical Sponsors (2003)</h2>
    <p>The Sponsors Luncheon was traditionally held the Friday before the regatta at the St. Francis Yacht Club.</p>

